(Bosch &amp; Sande Lac.) P.E.A.S. Câmara
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3326E8AFFFAC10C7FD7FCDDFC92F2D4" pageId="10" pageNumber="235" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B973D01FFFAC10C7FD7FCDDFC92F2D4" blockId="10.[136,1452,878,1157]" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFFAC10C7FD7FCDDFDC8F5D9" authority="Bosch &amp; Sande Lac." authorityName="Bosch &amp; Sande Lac." box="[136,593,878,905]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Hypnum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="10" pageNumber="235" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="glossoides">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFFAC10C7FD7FCDDFEFAF5D8" box="[136,355,878,904]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">Hypnum glossoides</emphasis>
Bosch &amp; Sande Lac.
</taxonomicName>
was described as an Indonesian species distributed in Java (
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFFAC10C7BACFCDCFA06F5D8" author="Fleischer, M." box="[1267,1439,878,904]" pageId="10" pageNumber="235" pagination="1105 - 1729" refId="ref8364" refString="Fleischer, M. (1923) Musci Buitenzorg 4. Brill, Leiden, i - xxxi + pp. 1105 - 1729." type="book chapter" year="1923">Fleischer 1923</bibRefCitation>
). It was reported from 
<collectingRegion id="49ECF3E3FFFAC10C7E20FC20FD9BF5FC" box="[383,514,914,940]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49ECF3E3FFFAC10C7D62FC21FD0AF5FD" box="[573,659,915,941]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
provinces of 
<collectingCountry id="F33F7D91FFFAC10C7C6CFC20FCEFF5FC" box="[819,886,914,940]" name="China" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">China</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFFAC10C7CF9FC20FB3CF5FC" author="Redfearn, P. L. J. &amp; Wu, P. - C. &amp; He, S. &amp; Su, Y. - G." box="[934,1189,914,940]" pageId="10" pageNumber="235" pagination="183 - 185" refId="ref9448" refString="Redfearn, P. L. J., Wu, P. - C., He, S. &amp; Su, Y. - G. (1989) Mosses new to mainland China. The Bryologist 92: 183 - 185. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3243941" type="journal article" year="1989">
Redfearn 
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFFAC10C7B49FC21FBC8F5FC" box="[1046,1105,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">et al.</emphasis>
(1989)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFFAC10C7BBFFC21FA31F5FC" author="Wu, P. - C. &amp; Jia, Y." box="[1248,1448,914,941]" pageId="10" pageNumber="235" refId="ref9890" refString="Wu, P. - C. &amp; Jia, Y. (2004) Flora Bryophytorum Sinicorum, Vol. 8. Science Press, Beijing, pp. 1 - 482. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="2004">Wu &amp; Jia (2004)</bibRefCitation>
. Our examination of voucher specimens reveals that the distribution records of 
<collectingRegion id="49ECF3E3FFFAC10C7B5FFC04FB1AF580" box="[1024,1155,950,976]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">Guangdong</collectingRegion>
[
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFFAC10C7BCCFC05FA35F580" box="[1171,1452,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">P.L. Redfearn Jr. 34376b</emphasis>
(PE)] and 
<collectingRegion id="49ECF3E3FFFAC10C7FA5FC69FEC9F5A5" box="[250,336,987,1013]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
[
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFFAC10C7E3FFC69FD9BF5A4" box="[352,514,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">W.-X. Xu 6452</emphasis>
(PE)] by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFFAC10C7D2FFC68FCFEF5A4" author="Redfearn, P. L. J. &amp; Wu, P. - C. &amp; He, S. &amp; Su, Y. - G." box="[624,871,986,1012]" pageId="10" pageNumber="235" pagination="183 - 185" refId="ref9448" refString="Redfearn, P. L. J., Wu, P. - C., He, S. &amp; Su, Y. - G. (1989) Mosses new to mainland China. The Bryologist 92: 183 - 185. https: // doi. org / 10.2307 / 3243941" type="journal article" year="1989">
Redfearn 
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFFAC10C7D82FC69FC8CF5A4" box="[733,789,986,1012]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">et al.</emphasis>
(1989)
</bibRefCitation>
are based on misidentification. Both of the voucher specimens are identical to 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFFAC10C7EEDFC4CFD05F248" authorityName="W. R. Buck" authorityYear="1987" baseAuthorityName="Cardot" box="[434,668,1022,1048]" class="Bryopsida" family="Hypnaceae" genus="Phyllodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hypnales" pageId="10" pageNumber="235" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="species" species="lingulatus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFFAC10C7EEDFC4CFD05F248" box="[434,668,1022,1048]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">Phyllodon lingulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. While the voucher specimen [
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFFAC10C7CA4FC4DFAFEF248" box="[1019,1383,1022,1049]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">P.L. Redfearn Jr. &amp; Y.-G. Su 942</emphasis>
(PE)] used for 
<collectingRegion id="49ECF3E3FFFAC10C7FB8FB91FEA4F26D" box="[231,317,1059,1085]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
recorded by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFFAC10C7E92FB91FD00F26C" author="Wu, P. - C. &amp; Jia, Y." box="[461,665,1058,1085]" pageId="10" pageNumber="235" refId="ref9890" refString="Wu, P. - C. &amp; Jia, Y. (2004) Flora Bryophytorum Sinicorum, Vol. 8. Science Press, Beijing, pp. 1 - 482. [in Chinese]" type="book" year="2004">Wu and Jia (2004)</bibRefCitation>
is a species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFFAC10C7C1FFB90FB4BF26C" authority="Montagne (1841: 279)" authorityName="Montagne" authorityPageNumber="279" authorityYear="1841" box="[832,1234,1058,1085]" class="Bryopsida" family="Daltoniaceae" genus="Symphyodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hookeriales" pageId="10" pageNumber="235" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFFAC10C7C1FFB90FC56F26C" box="[832,975,1058,1084]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">Symphyodon</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFB940F0FFFAC10C7C8AFB91FB4BF26C" author="Montagne, J. F. C." box="[981,1234,1058,1085]" pageId="10" pageNumber="235" pagination="266 - 282" refId="ref9085" refString="Montagne, J. F. C. (1841) Seconde centurie de plantes cellulaires exotiques nouvelles, decade X. Annales des Sciences Naturelles; Botanique, ser. 2, 16 (5): 266 - 282." type="journal article" year="1841">Montagne (1841: 279)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It is in accord with the concept of 
<taxonomicName id="4C284682FFFAC10C7E72FBF4FE25F230" authorityName="Montagne" authorityYear="1841" box="[301,444,1094,1120]" class="Bryopsida" family="Daltoniaceae" genus="Symphyodon" kingdom="Plantae" order="Hookeriales" pageId="10" pageNumber="235" phylum="Bryophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B95CE113FFFAC10C7E72FBF4FE25F230" box="[301,444,1094,1120]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="235">Symphyodon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by its oblong-lanceolate leaves, serrate leaf margins and slightly decurrent bases, obvious double costae and proration at upper end of laminal cells.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
